Package org.sbml.jsbml.ext.multi

Provides classes for the Multi package.

The current version implemented follow the proposal by Nicolas Le Novère and Anika Oellrich. There is only few classes from the proposal and it need to be completed.

Since:
1.0
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BindingSiteSpeciesType
    A BindingSiteSpeciesType object is a binding site, and therefore its instance can further define the bindingStatus attribute and can participate a binding internally and explicitly in an InSpeciesTypeBond object, or externally and implicitly defined by an OutwardBindingSite object.
    CompartmentReference  
    InSpeciesTypeBond
    Defines a bond existing within a MultiSpeciesType.
    IntraSpeciesReaction  
    MultiASTNodePlugin  
    MultiCompartmentPlugin  
    MultiConstants
    Contains some constants related to the multi package.
    MultiModelPlugin
    In order to encode the structures needed to define and use multistate and multi-component complexes, the element model is extended to be linked to a list of MultiSpeciesTypes.
    MultiSimpleSpeciesReferencePlugin  
    MultiSpeciesPlugin
    A species in the Multi package is extended from a pool to a template or pattern which multiple pools may map to.
    MultiSpeciesReferencePlugin  
    MultiSpeciesType
    The element MultiSpeciesType, which is part of SBML Level 2 Version 4 specification, is not part of SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core any more.
    OutwardBindingSite
    A binding site not involved in any InSpeciesTypeBond object in the MultiSpeciesType referenced by a Species is an outwardBindingSite.
    PossibleSpeciesFeatureValue
    Each state feature (SpeciesFeatureType) also requires the definition of all the possible values it can take.
    SpeciesFeature
    Defines the state of a component in a species by selecting values from the listOfPossibleSpeciesFeatureValues of the referenced SpeciesFeatureType.
    SpeciesFeatureType
    A species type (MultiSpeciesType) can carry any number of features (SpeciesFeatureType), which are characteristic properties specific for this type of species (Species).
    SpeciesFeatureValue  
    SpeciesTypeComponentIndex
    Provides a way to identify or index a component within a MultiSpeciesType.
    SpeciesTypeComponentMapInProduct
    A speciesTypeComponentMapInProduct defines the mapping between a component in a reactant and a component in a product.
    SpeciesTypeInstance
    Provides a way to construct MultiSpeciesTypes and Species with multiple components.
    SubListOfSpeciesFeature
    Allows to regroup a set of SpeciesFeature that have a specific Relation between them.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BindingStatus
    The BindingStatus enumeration is used in the definition of the OutwardBindingSite class.
    Relation
    The Relation enumeration is used in the definition of the ListOfSpeciesFeatures class.
    RepresentationType
    The RepresentationType enumeration is used in the extension of the ci element.
